# agee browser extension — environment for the quiet gateway round-trip smoke.
# Copy to .env (git-ignored) and fill in. NEVER commit real secret values.
#
# Run the authenticated legs with:  node --env-file=.env scripts/smoke-gateway.mjs
# (Node 20.6+ loads --env-file natively; do not add dotenv.)

# Bearer token for the agent gateway. Required ONLY to confirm the two
# authenticated round-trip legs live:
#   1.2  command  -> POST /v1/voice/turns
#   1.3  describe  -> POST /v1/chat
# If unset, smoke:gateway still verifies /health (1.1) and the loud
# unauthorized-error path (1.4), and SKIPS 1.2/1.3 (it does not fail).
AGEE_GATEWAY_TOKEN=

# Optional: override the gateway base URL (defaults to the live gateway).
# AGEE_GATEWAY_URL=http://10.147.17.10:8788

# Optional: pin a Chrome for Testing binary if it is not in the puppeteer cache.
# AGEE_CHROME_PATH=

# NOTE: `npm run smoke:settings` (change settings by talking to the agent) needs
# NO secret from this file. It boots a LOCAL moa_gateway on a throwaway port with
# a throwaway token it generates per run, so it never reads AGEE_GATEWAY_TOKEN or
# the gateway's .env, and it deploys nothing.
